channel.title: Unexpected server responce?
channel.description:
Alright, I thought i did everything right but, then it started saying this "Unexpected server responce, please try a different level". I don't know what the hell that means. Iv'e been told that means that you'r server isn't online but, im pretty sure it is cause it's running the bottom
Every time i click the logon button on the webclient i made on Rswebclients it says connection recieved from and then my IP address... I downloaded No-Ip and made a host and stuff and i have it checked in the DUC whilst the server source is running in the bottom but, when i click to logon it says the unexpected server responce thing...can someone please help me? I would prefer teamviewer but, any type of help would suffice. thanks for reading :) -Shea

item.title: Unexpected server responce?
item.dc:creator: @whackatre Whackatre
item.description:
@whackatre wrote:

Unexpected server response is when your server sends a few bytes which the client isn’t configured to read them. Are you using the right source? Is UID checking enforced?
